  "text": "Also, for Internet auctions, Yokoo et al. pointed out the possibility of a new type of fraud called false-name bids that exploit the anonymity available on the Internet [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . False-name bids are submitted under fictitious names, e.g., multiple e-mail addresses. Such deception is very difficult to detect, since identifying each participant on the Internet is virtually impossible. Although several false-name-proof multi-unit auction protocols have been developed, they also assume quasi-linear utilities.",
